-- Canadian Home Prices Post First Gain in 7 Months, Teranet Says
-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 2013-04-17T13:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-17/canadian-home-prices-post-first-gain-in-7-months-teranet-says.html
Canadian home resale  prices  rose in
March for the first time in seven months, according to the
Teranet-National Bank Composite House Price Index.  Prices rose 0.4 percent based on an 11-city composite
 reading , according to a report today by Montreal-based National
Bank Financial, led by a 1.3 percent gain in Calgary. Increases
were broad-based, with prices up 0.7 percent in  Montreal , 0.2
percent in Toronto and 0.8 percent in  Vancouver .  Prices rose 2.6 percent in March from a year earlier, the
slowest 12-month gain since November 2009, according to the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theophilos Argitis in Ottawa at 
